# Cursor Rules for AIA-APP

## CRITICAL: Read DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md First

Before writing any code, ALWAYS read `docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md` first. This file contains all project decisions, preferences, and conventions.

## Key Principles

1. **NO GOD FILES** - Never create monolithic files. Always separate concerns into focused modules/services.
2. **Documentation in docs/** - All documentation files must be in the `docs/` folder (except README.md at root).
3. **Modular Architecture** - One service per domain, one route file per resource, focused components.

## Stack Decisions

- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + DaisyUI + Tailwind + Font Awesome (NO emojis in code)
- Backend: Node.js + TypeScript + Express + Prisma + PostgreSQL
- Hosting: Railway (backend/DB) + Vercel/Netlify (frontend)
- AI: OpenAI GPT-4 Vision API
- Pricing: DataForSEO + SERP API

## File Organization

- Documentation: `docs/` folder only
- Routes: `backend/src/routes/` (one file per resource)
- Services: `backend/src/services/` (one service per domain)
- Components: `frontend/src/components/` (reusable components)
- Pages: `frontend/src/pages/` (page components)

## Database

- PostgreSQL on Railway
- Local password: `123`
- ORM: Prisma
- 4 main tables: inventories, inventory_items, inventory_images, reports

## Code Style

- TypeScript strict mode
- kebab-case for files
- camelCase for variables/functions
- PascalCase for components/types
- NO `any` types
- Font Awesome icons (NO emojis)

## When Creating New Features

1. Check DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md
2. Create route in `routes/`
3. Create service in `services/`
4. Add types in `types/`
5. Write tests
6. Update documentation in `docs/`

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- ❌ God files (monolithic files doing everything)
- ❌ Documentation at root (use `docs/`)
- ❌ Business logic in routes (use services)
- ❌ Emojis in code (use Font Awesome)
- ❌ `any` types (use proper TypeScript types)
- ❌ Monolithic services (one service per domain)

